history.text: Hi!
Hi!
Have you seen the movie Dunkirk yet?
I am not sure, could you tell me a little about it and I will see if I can remember?
It's the movie by Christopher Nolan, about WW II
Rotten Tomatoes is giving it a 92%
Ah, ok. No, I don't think I have.
Would you say it was a documentry type movie?
You should definitely check it out. The critics like it too, calling it a "triumph in filmaking"
Sounds like the critics like it a lot. Do you know who stars in it?
Some great actors.Harry Styles,  Fionn Whitehead, Tom Glynn-Carney, Jack Lowdon
Ah, ok. I'm not real familar with thier work. But, I do like WWII movies.
Can you tell me any of the plot?
That's a start. As a preview, the Dunkirk evacuation occurred during the fall of France. Hundreds of thousands of Allied soldiers retreated to Dunkirk and anxiously awaited evacuation
Nolan tackles it from three perspectives: land, sea , and air
The movie has little dialogue
Sound like something you would like?
It does! I really enjoy movies that show different perspectives and how the people interact together.
I bet the lack of dialogue makes the movi feel very intense!
That's great. Yes! A critic quote: Nolan "surrounds his audience with chaos and horror from the outset"
I couldn't imagine how that must have felt to the people who lived it!
I bet! Would make you feel like it was happening to you.
Surreal. The movie actually does a great job of showing how different people react to such trauma
I'm really excited to see it now!
Do you know what year it came out?
Glad to hear it. It just came out last year (2017)
It's the best war movie I've seen in some time.
Thank you for explaining it to me so well.
Happy to try to convey without giving too much away
I'm really intrigued to watch it now, and no, I don't think you gave away any spoilers. Thanks!!
For sure. Let me know if you have any follow up questions
I'm seeing the movie is also available in IMAX
I can only imagine that
Oh wow!! Indeed! That would be an amazing experience. Talk about being imersed in the action.
Pretty quick too. Action from start to finish for just over 100 minutes
I think I would want to see it in IMAX first then watch it again with a regular screen.
Great call
Pleasure talking and hope you enjoy it
Ha! That's pretty short for a movie. They must really cram a lot into those 100 mins.

uid1response.feedback: The other person did a great job of explaining the movie to me without giving away any spoilers. I feel like this is a movie I would really enjoy and the other person gave me a lot of useful information about the movie.
